creator: Sir Arthur Conan Doyle
description:
LibriVox recording of The Guards Came Through and other Poems by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle.
Read in English by Greg Giordano; Ken Masters; Mark F. Smith; Jairus Amar; Julia Niedermaier; Martin Geeson; Anusha Iyer; Jordan Heron; Rosslyn Carlyle
This is a volume of poems by Arthur Conan Doyle, published in 1919. Many of them concern wartime experiences. - Summary by Carolin
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (25MB)
